section.text:

  Section 137 of the Higher Education Act of 1965 (
  20 U.S.C. 1015f
) is amended—

paragraph.text:
providing grants to eligible students attending institutions of higher education or participating
			 in programs of study abroad that are approved for credit by institutions
			 of higher education at which such students are enrolled;

a description of how the grant funds will assist the State in meeting its goals for college
			 affordability, including measures to minimize tuition increases and
			 measures to increase the availability of need-based student aid;

a description of the process the State will use to make subgrants to eligible institutions or
			 consortia of eligible institutions, including eligible institutions
			 described in paragraphs (1) through (7) of section 371(a);

a description of how the State will evaluate the effectiveness of such subgrants and how the State
			 will disseminate information on promising practices developed as a result
			 of such subgrants;

subparagraph.text:
for such fiscal control and fund accounting procedures as may be necessary to assure proper
			 disbursement of and accounting for Federal funds paid under this subpart;
			 and

paragraph.text:
information, as determined by the State in consultation with stakeholders, on student outcomes,
			 including enrollment, participation, and completion rates, disaggregated
			 by race, ethnicity, disability status, and socio-economic status;
